    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "FROM:\nVirginia Y. Black\nPublic and Community Relations Director\nLOS ANGELES DEPARTMENT OF AIRPORTS\n#1 World Way - Los Angeles\n90009\nTelephone: (213) 646-5260\nTERMINAL I--First new domestic airline terminal to be built at Los\nAngeles International Airport in two decades, the 360,000 square-foot\nTerminal 1 (center) became operational January 23, 1984, as part\nof the\nairport's $700 million improvement program. Constructed at a cost of\n$46.3 million, and as the new home for Air Cal, Muse Air, PSA, Southwest\nAirlines and USAir, Terminal 1 has 14 aircraft gates\nand the capacity to\naccommodate more than 6 million annual passengers.\n#\n#\n412602002\nJEF: rh\n6/6/84\n# 32073W"
    ],
